I realize `ttwu_pending` is cleared at the start of `sched_ttwu_pending`, so it's unreliable. Better approach: check `nr_running` after wake — if wakelist was used, `sched_ttwu_pending` is still spinning on `on_cpu`, so the task hasn't been activated yet (nr_running stays 1). If direct activation, task is enqueued synchronously (nr_running becomes 2).

